      "content": "I am sorry you feel this way, but it is a common experience for researchers to hit a fundamental error that invalidates years of work. While it is painful, the most effective path forward is to acknowledge the mistake and allow yourself to rest before moving on. Many people find that sharing their story with a trusted friend or therapist can help them regain a sense of identity beyond their research. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who specializes in academic burnout.",
      "source": "target",
